reviews.text: Dinner with family in this Michelin Guide 1-starred seafood restaurant. Their food are really yummy, excellently cooked & presented 😋😋😋😋😋😋 & staff service is excellent too. It's my second time be there & my last time was 3 years ago. Highly recommended 👍👍👍

This seafood restaurant really deserves 1star from Michelin Guide. The foods are really tasty and yummy. As you can see, the chef was also putting effort on the presentation of the dishes. The small shortcoming may be the overcooked fish. Anyway, Should give them a try if you have chance to pass by.
Love the food and the stuff are very helpful and nice

Really luxurious seafood restaurant in everything from the décor to the plating to the service. Considerably better than any of the restaurants at the pier, however the view is not as good during daytime. If you are the during night time the upper floors allow a great view of Sai Kung as it lights up in the evening, which adds a lot to a meal here.

Not nice as expected and overpriced! Environment is not that great too!
If your money is easy money, you can go.

reviews.text: 新鮮好味😀

地方舒適清潔，門外有廿多個咪錶停車位，亦有代客泊車服務。

食物味道好份量足，價錢合理。推介菜式：椒鹽鮑魚，芝士海蝦米粉底（炸米粉恰到好處，鬆化不膩）。前菜墨魚煎餅及脆皮滑豆腐值得一試。
